What is true of a spontaneous process is also true of an evolutionary one. Evolution is not a force or a power but a process. It is a process of trial and error. It is a process of mutation, variation, selection, and retention. This is the way in which the evolutionary process is observed. This is the way in which it is described. This is the way in which it is understood. What is the evidence for this claim? The evidence is the fact that the process of evolution is observed.

What is the moscow treaty on strategic offensive reductions? The Moscow Treaty on Strategic Offensive Reductions (START) is a bilateral treaty between the United States and Russia that was signed in Moscow on 24 May 2002. The treaty was the follow-up to the Strategic Arms Reduction Treaty (START I). The treaty was signed by President George W. Bush and Russian President Vladimir Putin.
